The paper focuses on designing a high-performance DNN accelerator that can adapt to a wide range of DNNs with varying layer shapes and sizes, while also addressing the architectural bottlenecks in existing designs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of AR (Hardware Architecture), CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), AI (Artificial Intelligence), NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and SY (Systems and Control).
